         <abstract>
            <p>We present formulations of the Trotter-Kato theorem for approximation of linear C&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt;-semigroups which provide very useful framework when convergence of numerical approximations to solutions of PDEs are studied. Applicability of our results is demonstrated using a first order hyperbolic equation, a wave equation and Stokes' equation as illustrative examples.</p>
          </abstract>
